snippet.textDisplay: Time to set the record straight on ages here. 30 year old fathers aside, it's 50 YEAR OLD fathers and grandfathers who are excited most about this movie. This movie is for those who grew up solidly in the Cold War of the 1980's when the Soviet Union was at the nearest point of collapse.  The USA and USSR could have destroyed the world together many times over with nuclear weapons. Our generation is truly the VERY LAST and  FINAL "Great Generation" because we lived through this every day growing up under the very real threat of "Mutually Assured Destruction". The best times ever and I can remember seeing Top Gun for the first time and being ready to  enlist!!!!

snippet.textDisplay: I just hope it is as good as the trailer looks. While Super Hornet does not have the screen presence of The Mighty F-14, this looks just great. Seemed like Mission Impossible to make worthy sequel to Top Gun two years ago...hats down to Tom Cruise for his dedication and energy (and for adding the P-51:-D). Count me in - will go to see it four to five times I guess.
